{{MRfD|SpongeBob SquarePants}} {{Infobox Website | name = SpongeBob.com | logo = | screenshot = | caption = | url = http://spongebob.nick.com/ (US) | commercial = Yes | type = [[URL redirection]] | registration = | owner = [[Nickelodeon (TV channel)|Nickelodeon]] | author = | launch date = {{start date|2009|01|05}} | current status = Open }} '''''SpongeBob.com''''' is a website owned by [[Nick.com]]. The website launched on January 5, 2009 and [[URL redirection|redirects]] the user to their corresponding national website, based on the user's [[IP Address]]. Users from the United States are [[URL redirection|redirected]] to http://spongebob.nick.com/, and users from Asia will be redirected to http://spongebob.nick-asia.com/. [[Canada|Canadian]] users will be redirected to http://spongebob.ytv.com/, where the page is hosted on [[YTV (TV channel)|YTV]], a Canadian [[television channel]] where ''[[SpongeBob SquarePants]]'' is broadcasted and Australian users are redirected to http://www.nickelodeon.com.au/spongebob. Effective September 28, 2009, the Nickelodeon 'splat' became extinct from the site.
==Format== SpongeBob.com is the website of the TV series, ''[[SpongeBob SquarePants]]''. It is intended to be used by children six years old or older. The websites feature videos, games, characters, and broadcast schedules. In the "Videos" sections of the website, there are mostly episodes of ''SpongeBob SquarePants''.
